Pro/Side Hop Counter with In and Out

We now use our move that we learned (see previous breakdown video) and put it into a Drill situation to start the build up process and get our players comfortable with it before using it in a game. 
Our players attack with a between the legs, then once they get into the paint they make the pro/ side hop but keep the ball alive so once the defender reacts they hesitate and make a quick In and Out dribble to attack. 
They attack the help defender straight on making a hard dribble into their pro hop to rise up for a touch finish.
